    "Utilizing standard approaches, this generically leads to an exponential decay, in agreement with exact results [52] and with our exact numerical results.",
    "Furthermore, we investigated the effect of disorder on the relaxation dynamics, where the behavior at large values of disorder strength is consistent with localization.",
    "Most notably in the context of the current study, the expected absence of thermalization is evident in the stationary form of the quasi-momentum distribution for one or two charge carriers that exhibit resilient finite-momentum peaks.As our main results, we considered two modifications of the initial state: either by going to a finite density of charge carriers in a ferromagnetic background or by injecting one electron into an antiferromagnetic background, the time evolution of observables becomes consistent with thermalization.",
    "This is corroborated by a direct comparison with expectation values computed in a compatible canonical ensemble and an analysis of the gap ratio.As an outlook, we envision to add optical phonons to the problem, which would allow us to study the competition between two bosonic baths.",
    "Technically, this could be simulated with advanced matrix-product state methods for phonons [84][85][86][87] or a classical treatment of the phonons in the spirit of multitrajectory Ehrenfest dynamics [88] or the truncated Wigner approximation (see, e.g."
